description.narrative: To deliver direct environmental and economic benefits from the integration of biogas in farming and cooking in rural households. In addition, the project aims to reduce greenhouse gas emissions through methane combustion and reduced burning of coal and firewood in the project areas.

condition.narrative: All project households will be ensured a national level grant for the biogas digester in an equitable manner and in an amount thatshall be adequate for such purposes.
Annual budgets will be provided specifying funding need and funding source for each project activity.
Annual project counterpart budgets will be included in each project province's and county's annual budget.
Financing for households shall follow procedures agreed with the Bank and project entities shall enter into an implementationagreement with all project households.
Management organizations, including the PLG, PMO, PIO, PIG will be maintained throughout the project implementation.
Project entities shall implement the project consistent with the Project Implementation Manual.
Project entities shall prepare annual work programs for the Bank's review.
Project impact monitoring reports shall be submitted to the Bank year 0, 3, and at the end fo the project.
Project progress and impact M&E will be carried out according to a methodology agreed upon by the Bank.
Project progress reports shall be submitted to the Bank on a semi-annual basis.

baseline.value: 4 ton CO2 equivalent per household per year.

title.narrative: Chemical fertilizers and pesticides used by project households.

target.value: Decrease by 20-30% per target household and year.

title.narrative: Reduction in greenhouse gas emissions as CH4 is extracted from wastes and converted to CO2 as it is burnt as fuel.

baseline.value: Currently households emit about 4 ton CO2 equivalent/household/year.

target.value: Accumulative. Year 3: 600,000 ton CO2 equivalent per year; Year 5: 800,000-1,000,000 ton CO2 equivalent per year.

actual.value: 920,000 ton CO2 equivalent per year (2ton for each hh)

title.narrative: Raised hh disposable income as fuel costs, gathering time, and cooking time are reduced and as biogas slurry replaces synthetic fertilizer and pesticides.

baseline.value: Households buy abt. 1,500kg coal/year. Spend about 15% of cash revenues for chemical fertilizer and pesticides. Spend 1-3hrs/dayon collecting firewood and 3-4 hrs/day for cooking.

target.value: Per project hh, cost for coal will decrease by 30-50%, cooking time by 1-1.5 hrs/day, time for firewood collection by 2 hrs/day.Part of chemical fertilizer+pesticides is replaced by biogas slurry.

actual.value: Compared the fuel costs between project hh and non project hh, the former is 262 RMB less than the latter, which decreases 50.7%.(Fuel comprised of charcoal, gas and wood)

title.narrative: Improved quality of life in rural households as kitchens, farmyards, and surrounding environments are cleaner and healthier.

baseline.value: Living conditions are quite dirty, especially in summer due to manure management. There is a lot of smoke in the kitchens whilecooking.

target.value: In each project village and for project households, living conditions are significantly better. Manure management has improved sothat surroundings are much better.

actual.value: The incident of cough among project households decreased by 7.7%

title.narrative: Project progress and impact monitoring carried out with an MIS and M&E system agreed upon with the Bank.

target.value: Reports generated by MIS and M&E and submitted to the Bank in a timely manner.

Changes in project hh cash expenditures on fuel.
